cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use Make Me Unicorn in your research or product, please cite it as below."
title: "Make Me Unicorn: An Open-Source Launch Checklist and Operating System for Solo SaaS Builders"
abstract: >-
  Make Me Unicorn (MMU) is an open-source command-line tool that helps solo SaaS
  founders catch what AI-generated code misses before launch. It provides a
  534+ item checklist across 15 categories (frontend, auth, billing, security,
  SEO, legal, observability, and more), organized into 6 launch gates
  (Problem Fit, Build Fit, Revenue Fit, Trust Fit, Growth Fit, Scale Fit).
  MMU is distributed as a Python CLI (`pip install make-me-unicorn`) and
  integrates with Claude Code as a plugin and with the Model Context Protocol (MCP)
  as a server.
